1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:02,067
<i>Who else could be
Sandro's accomplice?</i>

2
00:00:02,167 --> 00:00:04,100
<i>I wasn't able to dig up
those details.</i>

3
00:00:04,233 --> 00:00:07,267
<i>But if you want,
I'll continue my work.</i>

4
00:00:08,167 --> 00:00:08,900
<i> Do it.</i>

5
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:11,400
[GROANS] My granddaughter...

6
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:13,567
<i> Happy birthday.</i>

7
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:15,467
[GROANS]

8
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,733
<i>You! You have a shadow
following you.</i>

9
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,067
<i> Be careful.</i>

10
00:00:19,300 --> 00:00:21,300
<i>Looks like this guest
might cause trouble.</i>

11
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,967
<i>The staff said Luna
knows this person.</i>

12
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:25,567
- [SLAPS]
- Ouch!

13
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:26,600
<i> It's dead.</i>

14
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:28,733
<i>I just really can't leave Jade
with that man.</i>

15
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:31,367
<i>Every time they're together,
something bad happens.</i>

16
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:32,800
<i> - Jade, there's poop!
- Where--</i> [SCREAMS]

17
00:00:32,933 --> 00:00:34,967
<i>Ugh! We almost ran
into bad luck again.</i>

18
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,233
<i> Ugh! Bad luck!</i>

19
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:40,800
<i>Oh no, sir, you just
happened to step on it.</i>

20
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:44,633
- [KIKO PANTS]
- [JADE] Sir, are we still far?

21
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:47,800
- Just a bit, ma'am.
- You're so far ahead. Wait.

22
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,267
W-Wait.

23
00:00:49,367 --> 00:00:51,167
Wait, mister. [PANTS]
Wait, wait.

24
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:53,800
- Ouch. Give that to me.
- No, I can handle it.

25
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,233
No, I can handle it.

26
00:00:55,367 --> 00:00:57,000
[PANTING]

27
00:00:57,167 --> 00:00:58,100
Wait, I'm thirsty.

28
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,933
[PANTING]

29
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:04,667
Hmm.

30
00:01:04,833 --> 00:01:06,100
[SATISFIED SIGH]

31
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,567
[EXHALES]

32
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:08,467
I can handle it.

33
00:01:08,567 --> 00:01:10,167
Wait, let me just
get some tissue.

34
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:12,033
I'm sweating like crazy.

35
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,100
[EXHALES]

36
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:17,367
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

37
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,700
[SNICKERS] Wow.

38
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:22,700
The old man really had us climb
the mountain on Friday the 13th

39
00:01:22,867 --> 00:01:24,033
of all days.

40
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,033
He said

41
00:01:26,167 --> 00:01:29,200
the effect of this necklace
will only last until later.

42
00:01:29,333 --> 00:01:31,433
So we need to do
the ritual right away

43
00:01:31,567 --> 00:01:33,533
so the bad luck
will completely go away.

44
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:36,500
Do you believe it now?

45
00:01:38,067 --> 00:01:39,500
A little.

46
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:41,167
- I can handle this.
- [BAG ZIPS]

47
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:42,700
Really?

48
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:43,700
Uh...

49
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:47,200
Because so far,
nothing unlucky has happened

50
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:49,733
even though the two of us
are together, right?

51
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:52,400
[CHUCKLES] You're right.

52
00:01:53,767 --> 00:01:55,033
Right?

53
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,167
Let's go.

54
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,233
[JADE] Mister!

55
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:58,500
Mister, wait!

56
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,233
You're so fast.
Are you in a hurry?

57
00:02:00,367 --> 00:02:02,233
- We're here.
- Really?

58
00:02:02,367 --> 00:02:03,967
- Yes, ma'am.
- Oh my god.

59
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,300
- Finally.
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]

60
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:07,033
- Enjoy.
- [PANTING]

61
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,733
- Wow.
- Wow.

62
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:14,900
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

63
00:02:15,067 --> 00:02:16,533
Kiko, it's so beautiful here.

64
00:02:19,633 --> 00:02:26,033
- [SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

65
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:28,767
[JADE CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

66
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:29,933
It's so beautiful.

67
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:37,933
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,967
Rude?

69
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:32,500
Oh, yeah!

70
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:34,133
Handsome?

71
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:37,333
Not really.

72
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:38,933
You're not available?

73
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:41,000
- That's what I thought too.
- [MARTIN] Any update?

74
00:03:41,167 --> 00:03:42,100
[GASPS]

75
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,767
Okay, okay, bye.

76
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:45,767
Sir.

77
00:03:45,867 --> 00:03:47,000
Sir, I'm sorry.

78
00:03:47,167 --> 00:03:51,233
I couldn't find anyone
suitable for you to date.

79
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:53,267
Miss Isla Kaluguran is kind,

80
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:55,133
but she's not available.

81
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:58,133
Miss Isla Solara is sick.

82
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:00,033
You might catch it.

83
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:02,300
Miss Puerto Felicia...

84
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:04,767
[SIGHS]
...has a contest to join.

85
00:04:05,467 --> 00:04:07,600
- Uh, Miss Grand--
- Wait.

86
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,300
You know a
Miss Grand International?

87
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,600
Sir, I'm not finished yet.

88
00:04:12,733 --> 00:04:15,200
Miss Grande Mucho 2024...

89
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:18,867
looks more muscular than you.

90
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,100
- But she's smart--
- Stop it!

91
00:04:21,233 --> 00:04:24,333
Take care of the wine
I'm giving to Uncle Ronald.

92
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:25,533
Come back right away.

93
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:27,467
Don't go wandering off
somewhere.

94
00:04:29,533 --> 00:04:31,867
Wait, sir, what about your date?

95
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:32,800
Forget it.

96
00:04:32,933 --> 00:04:34,900
I'll face Uncle Ronald alone.

97
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:36,900
- [GASPS] Yes!
- What do you mean "yes"?

98
00:04:37,933 --> 00:04:39,400
Yes...

99
00:04:40,367 --> 00:04:43,567
I'll go buy the wine you're
giving to Uncle Ronald--

100
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,300
- I mean Sir Ronald.
- That's better.

101
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:47,567
- Go on, hurry up.
- Yes, I'll hurry.

102
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:55,000
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

103
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,133
Sorry, sir.

104
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:58,067
[GASPING]

105
00:05:03,767 --> 00:05:11,000
[AMBIENT MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,100
Let's do it.

107
00:05:15,233 --> 00:05:16,733
Uh, what does it say there?

108
00:05:17,967 --> 00:05:18,933
Let me see.

109
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:22,767
What is this?

110
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:27,233
It looks like some kind
of sundance.

111
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:30,000
Because look, there's a sun,

112
00:05:30,133 --> 00:05:34,200
then there are different poses
we need to do,

113
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:35,933
so we have to dance.

114
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,233
Come on, let's do it.
We might run out of time.

115
00:05:39,333 --> 00:05:41,633
Wait, we're going to dance here
and the bad luck disappears?

116
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,233
That's what the mister said.

117
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,600
- Okay, let's go.
- Come on.

118
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,533
- Let's go, the sun is setting.
- Okay.

119
00:05:47,667 --> 00:05:49,567
- First...
- How?

120
00:05:49,667 --> 00:05:51,600
- How?
- Let's turn.

121
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:53,367
- Turn like that, four times.
- Okay.

122
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:54,533
- Game.
- Okay.

123
00:05:54,667 --> 00:05:55,800
- One...
- One...

124
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,600
- Two...
- Two...

125
00:05:58,333 --> 00:05:59,967
- Three...
- Three...

126
00:06:00,133 --> 00:06:01,100
- Four...
- Four...

127
00:06:01,233 --> 00:06:02,700
Then the next...

128
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:05,967
Uh...

129
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,467
- [KIKO] What now?
- It's like...

130
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:09,067
Like this, maybe?

131
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:17,933
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

132
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:39,833
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

133
00:06:54,833 --> 00:07:01,800
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

134
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:23,733
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

135
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:42,667
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

136
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:04,700
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

137
00:08:05,367 --> 00:08:09,867
[HEART BEATING]

138
00:08:19,633 --> 00:08:26,433
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

139
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:39,800
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

140
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:57,500
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG?"
CONTINUES]

141
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:06,267
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,167
Uh...

143
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:11,500
It's done.

144
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:12,900
[CHUCKLING]

145
00:09:20,167 --> 00:09:27,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

146
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,900
The curse should be lifted
by now, right?

147
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,067
I hope so.

148
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:32,400
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

149
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:34,033
[AWKWARD CHUCKLE]

150
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:40,733
Are you really
leaving that fast?

151
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,567
Is that the only reason
why you came here?

152
00:09:42,567 --> 00:09:43,933
Thank you, guys.

153
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,500
You made my birthday meaningful.

154
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,333
Ah...

155
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:49,433
Thank you for coming
to Hotel 88.

156
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:53,367
Take care.

157
00:09:55,033 --> 00:10:00,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

158
00:10:00,033 --> 00:10:02,000
Hey, why are you spacing out?

159
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,300
What's the matter?

160
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,833
Were you affected by
what Maria said?

161
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:08,433
You know, it's okay
to be scared because--

162
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:09,800
Are you talking
about the shadow?

163
00:10:10,433 --> 00:10:13,033
Whatever danger she's talking
about isn't true.

164
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:15,667
You can't be too sure, Justin.

165
00:10:15,667 --> 00:10:18,467
You still have
to be careful in life.

166
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:22,033
Hey, where are you going?

167
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:23,567
I'm going back to my place.

168
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:26,367
[CHESKA] Take care!

169
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:28,700
Hey, watch out for the shadow!

170
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:34,733
[CAR BEEPING]

171
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:36,767
I'll double-check
the setup there myself.

172
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:37,867
Hurry up.

173
00:10:38,067 --> 00:10:39,800
Yes, sir. I'll be quick.

174
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:46,800
[PLAYFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:47,933
Documents.

176
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:50,700
Here.

177
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,633
Gift box.

178
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:53,633
[GIFT RATTLING]

179
00:10:53,633 --> 00:10:55,767
Okay, what else do I need?

180
00:10:58,567 --> 00:10:59,967
Ah! The wine.

181
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:01,567
[SARI] Where's the wine?!

182
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:02,567
Sari!

183
00:11:02,567 --> 00:11:04,567
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

184
00:11:04,567 --> 00:11:05,800
Universe!

185
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,533
Don't give me too much problems
at the same time, please!

186
00:11:08,933 --> 00:11:09,900
Okay.

187
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,400
Okay.

188
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:14,733
Sari, calm down.

189
00:11:15,067 --> 00:11:16,633
Keep calm, Sari.

190
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:18,033
Focus!

191
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:22,667
[WHINING] Where could
that wine be?

192
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:29,667
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

193
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:33,067
[PLAYFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

194
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,400
- [COFFEE DRIPS]
- [SARI EXCLAIMS]

195
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,867
[SCREAMS]

196
00:11:37,567 --> 00:11:38,967
Universe!

197
00:11:38,967 --> 00:11:41,567
I was just saying!

198
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:44,433
What kind of misfortune is this?

199
00:11:44,433 --> 00:11:45,800
What am I going to do now?

200
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,667
[SCOFFS]

201
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:49,833
Cloth! I need some cloth.

202
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:50,967
Where is it?

203
00:11:52,533 --> 00:11:59,467
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYS]

204
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:04,600
Luna, it's expected that
the hotel wouldn't profit yet

205
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,033
because we just reopened.

206
00:12:06,033 --> 00:12:08,400
There's still a lot of costs
that we need to earn back.

207
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:11,667
But we have to pay
the bank already.

208
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:14,467
They even sent a letter
about the loan.

209
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:15,867
Leave that to me.

210
00:12:15,867 --> 00:12:19,133
You, Martin, and I just need
to talk on how to fix it.

211
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:21,033
Top of mind...

212
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:24,000
it seems we already
need an investor.

213
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,533
Investor?

214
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:27,533
They will be a part owner too.

215
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,033
That depends on what
will be discussed.

216
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,700
Dad has friends who are
interested in investing here.

217
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,500
We can talk to them.

218
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:37,900
But we need to inform
Martin's side

219
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,467
because we are
under a partnership.

220
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:41,567
[CELL PHONE CHIMING]

221
00:12:41,567 --> 00:12:47,233
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

222
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:49,833
Okay, I'll head
to the office then.

223
00:12:49,867 --> 00:12:50,867
Are you sure
you'll be fine here?

224
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:52,667
Yes. Thank you.

225
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:09,200
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

226
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:15,733
Where are you?

227
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:18,633
How hard am I even
making you work?

228
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:21,000
Hello?

229
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,600
- Sari!
- [SARI] I'm on my way, sir!

230
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:24,100
<i> - I'm coming in already.
</i>- Sari!

231
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,900
<i> Sir, I'm here already.</i>

232
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:35,067
["SILONG KA MUNA" BY
BRYAN CHONG PLAYING]

233
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:57,033
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

234
00:13:58,667 --> 00:14:01,667
Sir, I'm sorry.

235
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:05,067
I accidentally spilled coffee
on my dress earlier.

236
00:14:06,100 --> 00:14:09,100
You might say that
I don't look presentable

237
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,633
to the people
you're meeting with.

238
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,667
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

239
00:14:13,667 --> 00:14:14,800
Okay.

240
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:18,433
Okay!

241
00:14:18,433 --> 00:14:22,000
Um, sir, here's the wine
and the token.

242
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Uh... what else do you
want me to do?

243
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,167
Do you need anything else?

244
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:27,767
No, just leave those there.

245
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,600
- Martin.
- Okay, sir. Uh...

246
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:32,100
Hi, Uncle. Good evening.

247
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,267
It's nice seeing you again.

248
00:14:33,267 --> 00:14:34,867
It's been a long while.

249
00:14:34,867 --> 00:14:36,833
- More than a year?
- Yeah.

250
00:14:37,267 --> 00:14:38,967
If I didn't have
a conference here,

251
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:40,167
you wouldn't even
pay me a visit.

252
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:42,233
[CHUCKLES FAINTLY] I'm sorry.
I was just really busy.

253
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:45,867
Is this your girlfriend that
Gerard's been talking about?

254
00:14:45,867 --> 00:14:47,033
What?

255
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,867
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

256
00:14:48,867 --> 00:14:51,833
[MARTIN] Yes, she's my...

257
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,833
girlfriend.

258
00:14:56,933 --> 00:14:59,133
Sari is my girlfriend.

259
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:03,967
Oh, that's right!

260
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:06,733
I'm so excited to meet you.

261
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,133
Nice to meet you too, Sari.

262
00:15:08,133 --> 00:15:09,733
[SARI] Nice to meet you too.

263
00:15:09,733 --> 00:15:16,667
["SILONG KA MUNA" CONTINUES]

264
00:15:23,133 --> 00:15:26,500
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

265
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:31,300
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [LIQUID TRICKLING]

266
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,233
[CHUCKLES]

267
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:44,200
Hey, bud.

268
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,667
Uh...

269
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:48,633
Margie.

270
00:15:50,333 --> 00:15:51,700
Hi, Margie. Uh...

271
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:53,700
Please put Edward's shoes away.

272
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:56,167
I don't want the house to smell.

273
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,367
[SIGHS]

274
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,667
[LIQUID TRICKLING]

275
00:16:07,533 --> 00:16:08,800
So...

276
00:16:09,567 --> 00:16:12,500
by the looks of it,
I guess it didn't go well.

277
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:17,667
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

278
00:16:18,767 --> 00:16:20,533
Tell me about it
when you're ready.

279
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:25,200
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

280
00:16:30,867 --> 00:16:33,700
- [LIQUID TRICKLING]
- [GULPING]

281
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:36,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

282
00:16:36,367 --> 00:16:38,533
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

283
00:16:40,633 --> 00:16:42,700
I know, Uncle,
there are many

284
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:45,333
island resort hotels
in the Philippines.

285
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,433
But what makes
Hotel 88 different

286
00:16:47,433 --> 00:16:50,600
is that it is truly an escape
from city life.

287
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:53,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,367
I've heard that before, Martin.

289
00:16:56,267 --> 00:16:57,533
The local vibes are different.

290
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:00,767
Island luxury
is what we call it.

291
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:04,600
Is that right, Sari?

292
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:07,367
Are you from here?

293
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:12,133
Yes, sir. Born and raised.

294
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,467
What do you do, Sari?

295
00:17:15,633 --> 00:17:16,833
Uh, Uncle...

296
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,633
I'm a hospitality
operations coordinator.

297
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,167
[RONALD]
So you're also in hospitality.

298
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:24,267
[SARI] Yes, sir.

299
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,367
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

300
00:17:27,367 --> 00:17:28,767
Oh, dessert.

301
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,467
[WHISPERS] Sir,

302
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:34,667
what's that shiny thing?

303
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,767
[WHISPERS] Gold flakes.

304
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:39,767
- Gold in ice cream! Fancy!
- Shh!

305
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:45,433
Uh, I mean,
ice cream is my favorite.

306
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:48,633
Sari. Sari, smaller bites,
please.

307
00:17:48,667 --> 00:17:49,800
It might be too cold.

308
00:17:50,967 --> 00:17:52,867
[SARI GROANS SOFTLY]

309
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,500
[MARTIN]
Sari, Sari, don't spit--

310
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,667
Don't spit it out.
It'll melt anyway.

311
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:02,833
- Sari, Sari--
- [SARI GROANING]

312
00:18:02,833 --> 00:18:04,300
Don't spit it out.

313
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,500
- Sari...
- [GROANING CONTINUES]

314
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,833
Give her water.
Drink some water, Sari.

315
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,700
Sorry. Sari isn't used to this.

316
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:15,167
Have some water.

317
00:18:16,367 --> 00:18:18,767
Does Carlos know
that this is what you do here?

318
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:25,633
[SARI BREATHING SHARPLY]

319
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:29,867
Sari, please. Drink more water.

320
00:18:29,867 --> 00:18:31,933
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

321
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:33,367
Cheers, man!

322
00:18:33,367 --> 00:18:35,367
Let's just enjoy, shall we?

323
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:37,867
Come on, guys.
It's happy hour!

324
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:38,833
[WOMAN] Oh!

325
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:41,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

326
00:18:41,033 --> 00:18:42,900
Hey, where are you going?

327
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:44,400
Take a shot first!

328
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:47,667
Come on, guys, let's do shots.

329
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,333
It's on me. I'll pay for it.

330
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:51,233
Sir, sir, I know this feeling.

331
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:53,333
You're drunk.
You've had enough to drink.

332
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,900
I'm not drunk.
I'm just having fun.

333
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,667
Can you not ruin my night?

334
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:59,067
Miss, let's do shots.

335
00:18:59,067 --> 00:19:00,367
- Argh!
- Sir!

336
00:19:01,633 --> 00:19:03,267
That's enough, alright?

337
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,400
What's wrong with you?

338
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,467
- That's enough!
- I just want shots!

339
00:19:06,467 --> 00:19:08,367
- What? Don't touch me!
- You don't know me.

340
00:19:08,367 --> 00:19:09,400
Why are you so cocky?

341
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,900
- You want more shots?
- I'm just having fun!

342
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:13,967
Justin! Justin! Chase! Chase!
That's enough.

343
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:16,067
This is a hotel, isn't it?
Can't I enjoy my time?

344
00:19:16,067 --> 00:19:17,900
You jerk! This isn't your house!

345
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:20,400
- That's enough.
- Miss, can I have a shot?

346
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,933
Justin, that's enough.
Let me handle this.

347
00:19:21,933 --> 00:19:24,433
- I'll talk to him!
- Give me a shot, please.

348
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:25,867
Chase, that's enough!

349
00:19:25,867 --> 00:19:27,867
You're not in Manila!
Get a grip!

350
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,600
You know what,

351
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,567
you talk as if you're so modest.

352
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:40,933
Hey, Luna or Solenn

353
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:43,100
or whatever pretentious name
you use,

354
00:19:43,100 --> 00:19:45,400
you are no different from me.

355
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:48,600
You're a drunk, a party girl--
I know all your dirt!

356
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,433
- That's enough.
- Enough?

357
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:51,633
Truth hurts, huh?

358
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:54,800
It's true, especially when
you were with your ex, Peter.

359
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,367
I said enough!

360
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:59,400
You had the best time
with your ex, who's an addict.

361
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,700
Maybe you're an addict too.

362
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,967
What?

363
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:04,000
Are you an addict too?

364
00:20:04,967 --> 00:20:06,667
Tell me.

365
00:20:06,667 --> 00:20:07,933
You're an addict now too, huh?

366
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:10,467
[BLOW LANDS]

367
00:20:10,467 --> 00:20:12,700
[JUSTIN GRUNTING]

368
00:20:12,700 --> 00:20:14,800
What now?! Come on!

369
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:15,800
Who's cocky now?!

370
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:18,367
- Drag him out of here!
- Bro, hold on.

371
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:19,967
Drag him out of here! Faster!

372
00:20:19,967 --> 00:20:22,467
- What? Come on!
- What now?! You animal!

373
00:20:22,467 --> 00:20:23,967
Get out of here!

374
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:24,967
Jerk.

375
00:20:24,967 --> 00:20:27,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

376
00:20:28,533 --> 00:20:30,833
[LUNA SOBBING]

377
00:20:30,967 --> 00:20:37,833
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

378
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:42,200
[WHIMPERING]

379
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,867
[GIO]<i> She had an ex
</i> before she left Manila?

380
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:53,867
[SOBBING]

381
00:20:54,000 --> 00:21:00,867
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

382
00:21:10,033 --> 00:21:11,733
Uncle, thank you for your time.

383
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:14,867
And I apologize for
what happened earlier.

384
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,467
Apologize for what?

385
00:21:17,933 --> 00:21:21,033
I actually had a lovely time
with the two of you.

386
00:21:21,167 --> 00:21:22,733
To be honest,

387
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,633
it's been a while since
I've had a...

388
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:28,567
a really fun dinner.

389
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:31,967
- [RONALD LAUGHS]
- That was funny to you?

390
00:21:32,067 --> 00:21:33,467
[SARI STUTTERS]
What I mean is...

391
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:37,000
Did you have a good time?

392
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:39,000
Oh, yes!

393
00:21:39,167 --> 00:21:40,500
[CHUCKLING]

394
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:43,667
You should have said so sooner.

395
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:45,867
I would've finished
my ice cream then.

396
00:21:46,033 --> 00:21:47,933
I couldn't finish it because
I felt so nervous.

397
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:49,833
[CHUCKLING]

398
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:52,333
All right, sir.

399
00:21:52,433 --> 00:21:54,700
I'm going to send you
some ice cream next time.

400
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,700
We have ice cream made
from coconut.

401
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,500
It may not have
gold flakes, but...

402
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,767
it's very refreshing.

403
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:02,433
No need, Sari.

404
00:22:02,567 --> 00:22:04,867
Just give me some when
I come back to this island.

405
00:22:05,767 --> 00:22:07,533
Yes, send me the proposal.

406
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:11,867
So when I come back here,
we'll just discuss it.

407
00:22:11,967 --> 00:22:13,767
Yes, I will.

408
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,933
We'll email it to you
right away. Thank you.

409
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:20,133
Carlos will be surprised
to see you here.

410
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:23,033
Uh, Uncle...

411
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:24,400
And for me?

412
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,933
That is a good thing.

413
00:22:27,067 --> 00:22:28,867
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

414
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:32,467
I hope you can influence Gerard
when it comes to women as well.

415
00:22:35,167 --> 00:22:36,633
Good night, Sari.

416
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:38,467
Good night to you two.

417
00:22:38,633 --> 00:22:40,633
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

418
00:22:40,767 --> 00:22:41,800
I'll see you.

419
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:50,267
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

420
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:51,900
Thank you, Sari.

421
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:54,567
You know what I mean.

422
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:57,400
Is this really happening?

423
00:22:57,533 --> 00:22:59,067
Did you really just say
the golden words?

424
00:22:59,200 --> 00:23:00,933
Yes.

425
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:02,900
And I won't say it again.

426
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,267
Thank you, sir!

427
00:23:05,367 --> 00:23:07,133
Thank you for saying thanks.

428
00:23:07,267 --> 00:23:14,333
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

429
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,633
That surprised me, universe!

430
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:21,333
You've filled my heart with
romantic vibes again!

431
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:29,600
Who really was that, Luna?

432
00:23:29,733 --> 00:23:31,867
Why does he have so much
to say about you?

433
00:23:32,033 --> 00:23:33,267
Justin, just ignore him.

434
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,867
Just ignore him?

435
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,367
He's tarnishing your name

436
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:38,533
and he's calling you
all sorts of things!

437
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,133
Just ignore him, Justin.
Stop it.

438
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:42,867
[JUSTIN SCOFFS]

439
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:44,867
Stop dismissing me!

440
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,633
Is he telling the truth?

441
00:23:48,733 --> 00:23:51,367
That your boyfriend in Manila
was an addict?

442
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:53,433
Is that what you were doing
when you left?

443
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:55,200
Were you just destroying
your life in bars?

444
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:56,567
[LUNA] Justin, please!

445
00:23:56,733 --> 00:23:59,567
Just worry instead if he files
a case for physical injury.

446
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:01,000
Think about the guests.

447
00:24:01,267 --> 00:24:04,067
They might think that our hotel
is a hub for drunkards.

448
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:07,400
If I hadn't stopped Chase,
you might've been hurt instead.

449
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:08,800
But now,
you're still thinking about--

450
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:11,200
Justin, you're suspended!

451
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:12,567
Huh?

452
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,567
Suspended?

453
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,833
You're being pulled from
your responsibilities

454
00:24:15,933 --> 00:24:19,067
effective immediately,
until you learn your lesson.

455
00:24:22,067 --> 00:24:23,167
Luna!

456
00:24:23,267 --> 00:24:30,333
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

457
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:33,500
<i> What do you want?</i>

458
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,167
<i> Put your life in order.</i>

459
00:24:35,300 --> 00:24:37,267
<i>How about yours?
Is it also in order?</i>

460
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,700
<i> Peter Montevilla.</i>

461
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:40,533
<i> Your family can't see you?</i>

462
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,067
<i> Others might see you then.</i>

463
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,000
<i> Me! We could be friends.</i>

464
00:24:44,100 --> 00:24:46,733
<i>You're still part of the
hotel's promotions, right?</i>

465
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:50,333
<i>I think you should always have
a connection to Hotel 88.</i>

466
00:24:50,467 --> 00:24:52,000
<i>What's your connection
to Sandro?</i>

467
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:55,600
<i>Don't you ever mention
that name inside this house!</i>

468
00:24:57,733 --> 00:24:59,533
<i> Hey! Who are you?!</i>

